    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;Source-specific routing, also known as Source Address Dependent Routing (SADR), is an extension to traditional next-hop routing where packets are forwarded according to both their destination address and their source address.  This document describes an extension for source-specific routing to the Babel routing protocol.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
